‚úÖ Exactly ‚Äî you‚Äôve nailed it. In forecasting, Best / Worst / Base = the forward-looking scenario planning bands, not just historical ranges.

So here‚Äôs how we set it up for 2025 ‚Üí 2030:
üîπ Base Case (Median / ‚ÄúMost Likely‚Äù)

    Project forward using the 2020‚Äì2025 median trend.

    August base ‚âà 9,963 visits/month, but we can apply a gentle decline (~2‚Äì3%/yr) if you want to reflect the downward slope seen in 2021 ‚Üí 2025.

üîπ Best Case (Optimistic)

    Project forward using historical maxima (e.g., August peak = 10,632 in 2021).

    Extend forward flat or with slight growth if leadership expects stronger engagement.

üîπ Worst Case (Pessimistic)

    Project forward using historical minima (e.g., August low = 7,389 in 2025).

    Extend forward flat or with small decay to model risk of further drop-off.

üìä Example for August (2025 ‚Üí 2030)

    Best Case: ~10,600 visits/month (if traffic holds near peak years)

    Base Case: ~9,900 visits/month (median ‚Äúmost likely‚Äù outcome)

    Worst Case: ~7,400 visits/month (continued troughs like 2025)

üëâ That‚Äôs the ‚Äúforecast cone‚Äù your boss/HR will understand:

    Base = median (normal workload)

    Best = peak (stretch workload)

    Worst = floor (lightest workload, best vacation window)

