Yep ‚Äî this is the piece that‚Äôs tripping you up, and it‚Äôs critical because it changes the size of the drop you can claim. Let‚Äôs break it down step by step.
1. What You Want to Compare

To say ‚ÄúAugust is below normal,‚Äù you need:

    August median (all August totals over 10 years)
    vs.

    Typical month median (all months, all years ‚Äî not just August).

That second number is the benchmark.
2. What Your Code Did

In the component you pasted, you wrote:

