    That‚Äôs 20 hand-picked values in the 15k‚Äì17k range.

    You sort them and take the middle = ‚Äútypical month median.‚Äù

    When you compare your August median (~10,475) to this inflated baseline (~16k), you get a ~30‚Äì40% drop.

Problem: this isn‚Äôt the real data. It‚Äôs just placeholders, so it exaggerates the dip.
