    Your current code: August looks 30% below typical (too extreme).

    True dataset: August is 3.5% below typical over 10 years.

    5-year subset: August is 9.1% below typical (the stronger case).

If you show HR the 30% drop, they can easily discredit it as wrong math. If you show -3.5% and -9.1% from real medians, they have no way out.
