Instead of hardcoding, calculate directly:

// All site-wide totals for all months, all years
const allTotals = fullData.map(month => month.total);

// True median of all months
allTotals.sort((a, b) => a - b);
const typicalMedian = allTotals[Math.floor(allTotals.length / 2)];

Now your August vs. typical comparison is bulletproof.

