ChatGPT said:

Great catch ‚Äî that‚Äôs exactly the kind of nit your boss or HR will seize on. Let‚Äôs pin this down clearly in the instructions so there‚Äôs zero ambiguity.

Here‚Äôs how to word it:
Clarification for Excel Summation

    Website Data (5-year-data-cleaned.txt)
    The file is structured with pages as rows and months as columns.

        To get monthly totals, you must sum vertically (down each column) across all 14 service pages.

        Example: In Excel, for column 2021-08, use =SUM(B2:B15) if rows 2‚Äì15 contain the page-level data.

    Tickets (ticketstats.csv)
    The file is structured with tickets as rows, each tagged with a date/month.

        In Excel, use a pivot table:

            Rows = Month

            Values = Count of Tickets

        Excel automatically aggregates counts vertically as part of the pivot.

üëâ Do you want me to embed this clarification directly into the reproducibility section of your justification doc, so there‚Äôs no wiggle room for misinterpretation?
